wikipedia_page.main: Laurie Dean Walker (born 14 October 1989) is an English professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for EFL League Two club Stevenage.

response: He returned to his former club Kettering Town in March 2012 to provide cover for the injured Laurie Walker, making his debut in their 1–3 defeat to Stockport County on 31 March.
*9 July: Portsmouth announces four players on trial: Jon Harley, Mustapha Dumbuya, Simon Eastwood and Laurie Walker.
